<b>API Resource:</b>
App Families
</p>

<h1>List app families (detailed view)</h1> 
</p>

<div class="span6"><p>

<b>API Platform Base Path:</b>
<div class="lead">
https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1/o/{org_name}
</div>

<b>API Resource Path:</b>
<div class="lead">
/developers/{developer_email}/app_families?expand=true
</div>

<p>
An expanded list of all App Families in an Organization, listing Apps in the collection 
</p>
</div>

<div class="spand6">
	<p>
<b>Verb:</b>
<span class="verb-GET">GET</span>
</p>
<b>Auth:</b>
Basic Auth
</p>




</div>



<div class="span12"><p>
Lists all app families in an organization, along with all apps contained in each app family.
</p>



<b>cURL:</b>
<pre>curl -u myname:mypass https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1/o/{myorg}/developers/{developeremail}/appfamilies?expand=true</pre>



<b>Sample Response:</b> 
	<pre>{
  &quot;appFamily&quot; : [ {
    &quot;apps&quot; : [ &quot;app2.1&quot;, &quot;app1.1&quot; ],
    &quot;name&quot; : &quot;appfamily1&quot;
  } ]
}</pre>



<b>Errors</b> 
	<pre>Failure 4xx with proper error message
{
  &quot;code&quot; : &quot;developer.service.DeveloperDoesNotExist&quot;,
  &quot;message&quot; : &quot;Developer named dev11@apigee.com does not exist in organization AutomationOrganization&quot;,
  &quot;contexts&quot; : [ ]
}

{
  &quot;code&quot; : &quot;developer.service.CompanyDoesNotExist&quot;,
  &quot;message&quot; : &quot;Company named testCompan11 does not exist in organization AutomationOrganization&quot;,
  &quot;contexts&quot; : [ ]
}</pre>

